<p>
  Version 2 of the RAiD API is now available, bringing new endpoints, improved
  performance, and expanded support for international research identifiers.
</p>
<p>
  The new version introduces a cleaner REST interface, better error messaging,
  and support for bulk operations — making it easier for institutions to
  integrate RAiD into their existing research management systems.
</p>
<p>
  Detailed API documentation and migration guides from v1 are available in the
  RAiD developer portal. Existing v1 integrations will continue to be supported
  until the end of 2026.
</p>
